[%csl Rd3][%cal Gc6b4]} 11. d3 Nb4 12. Bf1 c5 $11) 9... Nbd7 {[%csl Rd3][%cal
Gd7c5,Yc8a6] Another clever, flexible move.} (9... Bb7 {doesn't pose any
threats to the d3-weakness, so White can continue developing along the usual
