16. Nf4 Bxf4 17. exf4 Bxf3 18. Qxf3 $14 {[%csl Ra6,Yb2,Rc6,Rd5][%cal
Gf3d3,Gc1c2,Gf1c1, Yf1d1,Yd3d4] ½-½ (50) Adhiban,B (2603) -Puranik,A (2603)
chess24. com INT 2022. White has the better minor piece and clear pressure
against the black pawns.}) 16. gxf3 Rc8 17. Qd3 Nd7 {[%cal Gd8h4,Gd7e5]} 18. f4
$14 {[%csl Yb2, Rd6][%cal Yg1h2,Yf1g1,Ge2g3,Yb2g7] 1-0 (29) So, W (2812)
