needs to know a lot to equalize the game.}) 11. b3 O-O 12. Bb2 a6 ({Carlsen
showed the proper strategy for White in the case of} 12... Bg4 13. h3 Bh5 14.
Be2 {[%cal Ra7a6] Please note how White's up a tempo here compared to 10...Bg4
line. This already shows that 12...Bg4 is inaccurate.} Rc8 15. Nh4 Bg6 16. Nxg6
