{[%evp 0,37,20,22,14,10,10,10,10,14,10,4,47,36,37,29,30,-7,12,3,-1,17,45,24,39,
39,30,5,5,7,23,30,49,19,16,9,18,-11,-7,-13]} 1. Nf3 d5 2. e3 Nf6 3. c4 e6 4.
Nc3 c5 5. cxd5 Nxd5 {is the Semi-Tarrasch move. White could play 6.d4 now, but
that often leads to a reasonable hanging pawns middlegame for Black (after 6...
cxd4 7.exd4 Nxc3 8.bxc3 Qc7!, etc.) . Instead, I can recommend two different
approaches:} 6. Bc4 {White completes his developments and keeps d2-d4 as an
