{[%evp 0,38,22,15,14,13,13,13,39,48,42,23,26,26,23,18,23,31,23,21,6,-8,-8,-3,0,
0,0,0,0,-17,0,0,-52,-50,-9,-58,-18,-7,-15,-15,-15]} 1. Nf3 d5 2. e3 Nf6 3. c4
c6 {Players who normally play the Slav defense with Black will expect us to
play d2-d4 now or at some later point. However, the idea of the Keymer system
is to postpone this move until necessary or not play it at all. Therefore, we
start with a flexible move} 4. Nc3 {[%csl Gf1][%cal Rd5c4] waiting to see what
variation of the Slav defense our opponent will go for. It is important to
note that we avoid the Classical Slav (1.d4 d5 2.c4 c6 3.Nf3 Nf6 4.Nc3 dxc4)
with this move order because 4...dxc4 doesn't make sense for Black here. Those
who prefer the Semi-Slav usually continue} e6 5. b3 {We still don't commit our
d-pawn. Moreover, the deployment of the bishop on b2 helps us fight against
Black's ...e6-e5 advance.} Bd6 6. Bb2 O-O {[%cal Yf8e8,Ye6e5,Yb8d7,Yb8c6] The
most flexible continuation for Black.} ({In the case of} 6... Nbd7 7. Qc2 {
Black will find it trickier to advance his e-pawn because of his queenside
vulnerability (see 7...e5 below) .} O-O (7... Qe7 {doesn't change our general
plan.} 8. Be2 O-O (8... a6 {can be routinely answered with} 9. d4 {[%csl Ra6]
[%cal Rb7b6] since ...a6 doesn't fit well with Black's ... b6-plan. In case he
goes for the other developing scheme,} e5 10. cxd5 cxd5 11. dxe5 Nxe5 {White
gets a nice version of the Tarrasch IQP after} 12. Rd1 Be6 13. O-O Rc8 14. Qb1
$14 {[%csl Rd5] 1-0 (21) Bauer,C (2628) -Colmenares,A (2390) Zurich SUI 2018})
9. O-O {Black has tried many moves at this junction. The most accurate is
probably 9...Re8, which transposes to a position analyzed in the main line of
the 7...0-0 variation. Other prominent options are:} b6 (9... e5 10. cxd5 Nxd5
11. d3 (11. Ne4 $5 Bc7 12. Ng3 $13 {[%cal Gg3f5] might be a little more
accurate.}) 11... N7f6 12. Ne4 Bc7 13. a3 a5 $13 {[%cal Ye4d2,Yg2g3,Ye3e4] 1-0
(80) Zhou Jianchao (2615) -Zhang, Z (2374) Hangzhou CHN 2018, with a complex
reversed Hedgehog middlegame.}) (9... dxc4 10. bxc4 e5 {[%csl Rc8][%cal Rc8g4]
is a common plan for Black. However, it is not so effective here because he
